FBIS4-2454 "drchi069_k_94005" FBIS-CHI-94-069 Daily Report 11 Apr 1994 NATIONAL AFFAIRS Political & Social Crackdown on Dissidents, Reporters Arrested Crackdown on Dissidents, Reporters Arrested Spokesman on Xu Wenli HK1104022694 Hong Kong AFP in English 0217 GMT 11 Apr 94 HK1104022694 Hong Kong AFP English BFN [Text] Beijing, April 11 (AFP) -- Chinese dissident Xu Wenli, arrested Friday in Beijing, was picked up by police for having broken the law, the Chinese foreign ministry said Monday. "China public security organs summoned Xu Wenli according to law for he has violated relevant regulations on parole," a spokesman from the ministry told AFP. "This entirely falls within China's sovereignty and has nothing to do with China's relations with other countries," the spokesman said. Xu, 49, leader of the 1978-79 Democracy Wall movement in Beijing, was released on parole in May 1993 after 12 years in prison.
